 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Embedded Optimization Specialist, Human-Centered AI Toyota Research Institute 5 reviews Cambridge, MA 02139 Full-time Toyota Research Institute 5 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description The Toyota Research Institute (TRI) is an R&D enterprise designed to bridge the gap between fundamental research and product development. TRI has been launched with mandates to: 
 
 1. Improve the safety of automobiles, with the ultimate goal of creating a car that is incapable of causing a crash; 
2. Increase access to cars to those who otherwise cannot drive, including those with disabilities and the elderly; 
3. Help translate outdoor mobility technology into products for indoor mobility; and
 4. Accelerate scientific discovery by applying techniques from artificial intelligence and machine learning. 
 
Toyota believes artificial intelligence has significant potential to improve the quality of life for all people, bringing ease, comfort and safety to all aspects of life.  TRI's Human-Centered AI team  is researching and developing solutions to advance mobility for all. We are looking for great engineers with a variety of skills who are passionate about deploying systems improving the lives of millions. 
 Responsibilities: 
Develop and deploy optimization algorithms for real-time control 
Assist in the development of code-generation tools for optimization solvers 
Publish basic research related to these tasks. 
 Qualifications: 
Ph.D in Electrical Engineering, Computer Science, Operations Research, or related field. 
 Experience in 3 or more of the following: 
Model predictive control 
Convex optimization 
Numerical linear algebra 
High performance embedded computing 
Compilers 
Domain-specific languages 
